WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.564 --> 00:00:06.434
Your vitals are
good. heart rate. respiration.

2
00:00:06.517 --> 00:00:08.678
but you're burning O2
reserves. What's your ETA?

3
00:00:08.760 --> 00:00:11.502
Best guess.
ten. 15 minutes?

4
00:00:11.585 --> 00:00:13.912
It's already been
90. I'm calling you in.

5
00:00:13.995 --> 00:00:16.820
I'm doing elbow surgery
on a two-ton robotic arm

6
00:00:16.903 --> 00:00:18.773
in the cold vacuum of space.

7
00:00:18.855 --> 00:00:20.975
I'm not fixing a Chevy Chevelle.

8
00:00:21.058 --> 00:00:22.969
Down there. I don't have
to worry about my mechanic

9
00:00:23.052 --> 00:00:25.337
violently decompressing.
What's your point?

10
00:00:25.420 --> 00:00:26.957
This may take a minute.

11
00:00:27.040 --> 00:00:29.117
Problem will
still be there tomorrow.

12
00:00:29.200 --> 00:00:32.067
Technically. tomorrow
doesn't exist in space.

13
00:00:32.150 --> 00:00:33.977
Just "later."

14
00:00:34.059 --> 00:00:35.307
-so let's get 'er done.
-All right. you've got...

15
00:00:39.170 --> 00:00:40.708
Captain Stanton?

16
00:00:40.791 --> 00:00:42.910
-Captain Sta...
-You're cutting out.

17
00:00:42.993 --> 00:00:45.403
Let's reel you back in
and check your comms.

18
00:00:45.485 --> 00:00:46.483
Can you hear me?

19
00:00:46.566 --> 00:00:47.604
Captain Stant...

20
00:00:53.794 --> 00:00:55.149
Stanton. do you read me?

21
00:00:56.120 --> 00:00:57.450
Comms are down.

22
00:00:59.901 --> 00:01:01.023
Joyner!

23
00:01:01.106 --> 00:01:03.225
Joyner. behind you!

24
00:01:03.308 --> 00:01:04.471
Joyner!

25
00:01:04.554 --> 00:01:05.675
Oh...

26
00:01:16.145 --> 00:01:17.516
Joyner!

27
00:01:32.223 --> 00:01:33.386
I'm coming.

28
00:01:38.454 --> 00:01:39.826
I'm stuck.

29
00:01:39.908 --> 00:01:41.238
I'm all tangled.

30
00:01:42.193 --> 00:01:43.481
I'm tangled!

31
00:01:43.564 --> 00:01:45.144
Behind you!

32
00:01:45.226 --> 00:01:48.093
Move! Behind you!

33
00:02:04.835 --> 00:02:07.868
Six months ago.
the LAFD lost a hero.

34
00:02:07.951 --> 00:02:10.318
To honor his

35
00:02:10.401 --> 00:02:14.432
leadership. his service
and his sacrifice.

36
00:02:14.515 --> 00:02:18.005
from today on. this will
be the Robert Wade Nash

37
00:02:18.088 --> 00:02:19.542
Memorial Station.

38
00:02:27.186 --> 00:02:29.803
Now. Interim Captain Han

39
00:02:29.886 --> 00:02:31.008
will say a few words.

40
00:02:36.367 --> 00:02:37.364
Thank you. Chief.

41
00:02:43.263 --> 00:02:47.709
When Chief Simpson first spoke
to me about a tribute for Cap.

42
00:02:47.791 --> 00:02:50.160
we debated what to do.

43
00:02:50.243 --> 00:02:52.030
Should it be

44
00:02:52.112 --> 00:02:54.107
"The Robert Nash
Memorial Ladder Truck"?

45
00:02:54.190 --> 00:02:56.101
Or a building at the academy

46
00:02:56.184 --> 00:02:58.718
to inspire new recruits?

47
00:02:58.801 --> 00:03:01.750
And then I realized that
when I think of Bobby...

48
00:03:05.240 --> 00:03:07.983
...I picture him here.

49
00:03:08.065 --> 00:03:09.686
in this building.

50
00:03:12.137 --> 00:03:15.128
Manning that stove.

51
00:03:15.211 --> 00:03:17.662
