then we come back down.

525
00:26:53.159 --> 00:26:54.447
Huh.

526
00:26:54.529 --> 00:26:56.358
You know why he's
doing this. right?

527
00:26:56.441 --> 00:26:58.477
This is all damage control.

528
00:26:58.559 --> 00:27:00.429
Tripp Hauser is trying
to fix his image

529
00:27:00.512 --> 00:27:03.129
by sending a normal
person to space.

530
00:27:04.625 --> 00:27:07.118
Two normal people.

531
00:27:08.447 --> 00:27:10.275
I got him to give me a plus-one.

532
00:27:10.358 --> 00:27:12.436
What?

533
00:27:12.518 --> 00:27:14.887
You didn't think I was gonna
leave my rocket scientist wife

534
00:27:14.970 --> 00:27:16.133
down here on Earth?

535
00:27:17.213 --> 00:27:19.914
You're coming to space with me.

536
00:27:21.616 --> 00:27:23.361
I-I'm going to space?

537
00:27:23.444 --> 00:27:24.691
You're going to space. babe!

538
00:27:30.840 --> 00:27:31.878
I can't go to space.

539
00:27:33.124 --> 00:27:34.038
What?

540
00:27:34.121 --> 00:27:35.701
This has been your dream.

541
00:27:35.783 --> 00:27:37.487
Since... always.

542
00:27:37.569 --> 00:27:40.728
I am a serious scientist.

543
00:27:40.811 --> 00:27:44.259
Also. there are several
pending lawsuits

544
00:27:44.342 --> 00:27:45.796
between him and the
people I work for.

545
00:27:45.878 --> 00:27:47.624
I doubt he'd even let
me near the launchpad.

546
00:27:47.706 --> 00:27:49.411
Well. if you're not
going. I'm not going.

547
00:27:49.493 --> 00:27:51.196
Like hell you're not.

548
00:27:51.279 --> 00:27:53.357
One of us gets to go to space.

549
00:27:53.440 --> 00:27:54.437
Alone?

550
00:27:54.519 --> 00:27:56.348
Well. you still
have your plus-one.

551
00:27:56.431 --> 00:27:58.093
Take one of the guys with you.

552
00:27:58.176 --> 00:27:59.796
Yeah.

553
00:28:02.580 --> 00:28:04.407
But which one?

554
00:28:04.490 --> 00:28:05.903
Don't ask me to solve
all of your problems.

555
00:28:05.986 --> 00:28:07.897
I just gave up going to space.

556
00:28:13.547 --> 00:28:14.835
You're late.

557
00:28:14.918 --> 00:28:16.497
I had class.

558
00:28:16.579 --> 00:28:17.951
Oh. good.

559
00:28:19.321 --> 00:28:21.566
I was afraid maybe both
my children had abandoned

560
00:28:21.648 --> 00:28:23.227
their academic pursuits.

561
00:28:23.310 --> 00:28:24.515
What?

562
00:28:24.598 --> 00:28:26.426
Your brother. he dropped
out of high school.

563
00:28:26.509 --> 00:28:27.921
Since when?

564
00:28:28.004 --> 00:28:29.999
Day I turned 18.

565
00:28:30.082 --> 00:28:32.450
I got a job at that coffee
shop on La Brea instead.

566
00:28:32.532 --> 00:28:34.237
Is that why we always have
pastries at the house now?

567
00:28:34.319 --> 00:28:37.850
I'd take comfort in
not being the last one to know

568
00:28:37.933 --> 00:28:39.305
if it wasn't for the
fact that he was living

569
00:28:39.387 --> 00:28:41.465
under your roof
when it happened.

570
00:28:41.548 --> 00:28:43.252
How did you miss it?

571
00:28:43.335 --> 00:28:45.287
You're his mother.
How did you miss it?

572
00:28:45.370 --> 00:28:47.157
What is that supposed to mean?

573
00:28:47.239 --> 00:28:48.403
Maybe if you showed up

574
00:28:48.485 --> 00:28:50.480
a little bit more.
Mom. you'd have a clue

575
00:28:50.563 --> 00:28:51.768
about what goes
on with your kids.

576
00:28:51.851 --> 00:28:52.973
I show up.

577
00:28:53.055 --> 00:28:54.178
Every time we
invite you somewhere.

578
00:28:54.260 --> 00:28:55.466
you say no.

579
00:28:55.548 --> 00:28:57.169
Or. worse. you say yes

580
00:28:57.252 --> 00:28:59.163
-and then cancel an hour before.
-That is not true.

581
00:28:59.246 --> 00:29:01.364
Every Thursday night.

582
00:29:01.447 --> 00:29:03.691
May and I go to Hen and Karen's
house for a home-cooked meal.

583
00:29:03.774 --> 00:29:05.228
You are always invited.

584
00:29:05.311 --> 00:29:06.267
and you never show up.

585
00:29:06.350 --> 00:29:07.804
I know. but I...

586
00:29:07.887 --> 00:29:09.258
Sunday morning.

587
00:29:09.341 --> 00:29:10.837
FaceTime pancakes with Dad.

588
00:29:10.920 --> 00:29:12.083
Monday night. Bachelor

589
00:29:12.166 --> 00:29:14.326
-with Buck.
-Bobby's dedication ceremony.

590
00:29:20.807 --> 00:29:22.926
I'm sorry. I wanted to be there.

591
00:29:23.009 --> 00:29:24.712
-I really did.
-But you weren't.

592
00:29:26.415 --> 00:29:29.117
We lost Bobby and
we lost you. too.

593
00:29:29.199 --> 00:29:30.819
That is not true.

594
00:29:32.647 --> 00:29:35.390
I am here. now.

595
00:29:35.473 --> 00:29:37.467
and I am still your mother.

596
00:29:41.039 --> 00:29:42.035
Harry.

597
00:29:44.238 --> 00:29:46.730
You haven't been our
mother since Bobby died.

598
00:29:49.971 --> 00:29:52.049
Harry.

599
00:29:52.132 --> 00:29:53.835
Harry. wait.

600
00:30:05.385 --> 00:30:06.714
Oh!

601
00:30:06.797 --> 00:30:08.085
Yo!

602
00:30:11.948 --> 00:30:14.441
You heard about
Tripp Hauser's offer?

603
00:30:14.524 --> 00:30:16.020
The chief told me.

604
00:30:16.102 --> 00:30:17.557
Although. when he said it.
sounded more like an order.

605
00:30:17.639 --> 00:30:19.177
not an offer.

606
00:30:19.260 --> 00:30:20.673
Figured you might
want to be prepared

607
00:30:20.756 --> 00:30:22.002
for any close encounters
you might make up there.

608
00:30:22.085 --> 00:30:22.999
It was my idea.

609
00:30:23.082 --> 00:30:24.162
Didn't say it wasn't.

610
00:30:24.245 --> 00:30:25.409
Didn't say it was.

611
00:30:25.491 --> 00:30:27.195
So Karen must be super stoked.

612
00:30:27.278 --> 00:30:29.938
She finally gets to go to space.

613
00:30:30.020 --> 00:30:31.142
She said she can't go.

614
00:30:34.049 --> 00:30:34.964
What?

615
00:30:35.046 --> 00:30:37.042
Why not?

616
00:30:37.124 --> 00:30:40.157
Something about her
work and a lawsuit

617
00:30:40.240 --> 00:30:42.940
-with Hauser.
-But you still get to go. right?

618
00:30:43.023 --> 00:30:45.018
She wants me to.

619
00:30:45.101 --> 00:30:47.468
But I don't know that I
still want to go without her.

620
00:30:47.551 --> 00:30:49.297
Well. you
have your plus-one.

621
00:30:49.380 --> 00:30:50.543
You can bring someone else.

622
00:30:50.626 --> 00:30:51.914
Uh...

623
00:30:51.997 --> 00:30:53.244
someone else?

624
00:30:53.326 --> 00:30:54.698
Come on. Ravioli.

625
00:30:54.781 --> 00:30:56.982
I think we all know
who Hen's gonna take.

626
00:30:58.394 --> 00:30:59.434
Do we?

627
00:30:59.517 --> 00:31:00.556
Don't we?

628
00:31:01.967 --> 00:31:03.505
Uh. listen. Hen.

629
00:31:03.588 --> 00:31:04.918
don't let them
pressure you. okay?

630
00:31:05.000 --> 00:31:06.330
This is your decision.

631
00:31:06.413 --> 00:31:07.327
Thanks. Buck.

632
00:31:07.410 --> 00:31:08.948
I always got your back.

633
00:31:09.030 --> 00:31:11.108
And if you decide
to take me to space.

634
00:31:11.191 --> 00:31:12.977
-then...
-Unbelievable.

635
00:31:20.205 --> 00:31:21.410
What makes you think that?

636
00:31:21.493 --> 00:31:22.698
Um...

637
00:31:22.781 --> 00:31:24.443
He called about a smell.

638
00:31:24.526 --> 00:31:26.355
You know how many calls
we get about smells?

639
00:31:26.438 --> 00:31:28.847
"My neighbor smokes."
"My neighbor vapes."

640
00:31:28.930 --> 00:31:31.381
"My neighbor likes
to make spicy foods."

641
00:31:31.464 --> 00:31:33.084
People actually call about that?

642
00:31:33.167 --> 00:31:34.663
They call about everything.

643
00:31:34.746 --> 00:31:35.660
Said "25"?

644
00:31:35.743 --> 00:31:37.945
Gina Moningham. Wow.

645
00:31:38.028 --> 00:31:39.648
Here since the '90s.

646
00:31:48.165 --> 00:31:49.619
Hello? LAPD.

647
00:31:49.702 --> 00:31:51.198
Is anyone home?

648
00:31:52.817 --> 00:31:54.853
Maybe she went out.

649
00:31:56.806 --> 00:31:58.011
Open the door.

650
00:32:00.669 --> 00:32:02.789
O-kay.

651
00:32:03.869 --> 00:32:05.323
That's a smell.

652
00:32:07.442 --> 00:32:08.646
Hello?

653
00:32:10.931 --> 00:32:12.635
Is anyone here?

654
00:32:12.718 --> 00:32:14.337
LAPD.

655
00:32:18.284 --> 00:32:19.280
Ma'am?

656
00:32:21.400 --> 00:32:22.438
Gina?

657
00:32:27.133 --> 00:32:29.211
I'm Sergeant Athena Grant

658
00:32:29.293 --> 00:32:30.665
with the LAPD.

659
00:32:30.748 --> 00:32:31.994
Ma'am.

660
00:32:33.905 --> 00:32:35.359
Damn.

661
00:32:49.152 --> 00:32:50.482
Dispatch.

662
00:32:50.564 --> 00:32:53.140
This is 727-L-30.

663
00:32:53.223 --> 00:32:54.386
We have a 10-55...

664
00:32:59.039 --> 00:33:00.494
I got a pulse but barely.

665
00:33:00.577 --> 00:33:02.114
What the hell is that?

666
00:33:02.196 --> 00:33:03.485
I mean. it looks like
she's been dead for weeks.

667
00:33:03.568 --> 00:33:04.690
My guess?

668
00:33:04.772 --> 00:33:06.767
Necrotizing fasciitis.

669
00:33:06.850 --> 00:33:07.764
Bacterial infection.

670
00:33:07.847 --> 00:33:10.048
She's been rotting
alive in here.

671
00:33:10.131 --> 00:33:11.835
Alone.

672
00:33:11.918 --> 00:33:13.829
She's not
stable enough to move.

673
00:33:13.912 --> 00:33:14.951
Let's get
her heart rate up.

674
00:33:21.515 --> 00:33:23.218
Temp is way
down. Fluid in her lungs.

675
00:33:23.301 --> 00:33:25.046
I don't even know
how she's breathing.

676
00:33:25.129 --> 00:33:26.500
Get her prepped
for transcutaneous pacing.

677
00:33:26.583 --> 00:33:27.996
On it.

678
00:33:28.078 --> 00:33:30.115
♪ Are familiar faces ♪

679
00:33:30.198 --> 00:33:33.563
♪ Worn-out places ♪

680
00:33:33.645 --> 00:33:37.260
♪ Worn-out faces ♪

681
00:33:37.343 --> 00:33:39.089
-♪ Bright and early... ♪
-Set the pads.

682
00:33:39.171 --> 00:33:42.121
-Administer analgesic.
-Pulse is down to 43.

683
00:33:42.203 --> 00:33:43.824
Pressure dropping.

684
00:33:43.907 --> 00:33:48.602
♪ Going nowhere ♪

685
00:33:48.685 --> 00:33:52.964
♪ Their tears are filling
up their glasses ♪

686
00:33:53.047 --> 00:33:54.667
♪ No expression... ♪

687
00:33:54.750 --> 00:33:56.786
Pads in
place and secure.

688
00:33:56.868 --> 00:33:59.071
Checking ECG complex.

689
00:33:59.153 --> 00:34:00.525
♪ Hide my head ♪

690
00:34:00.608 --> 00:34:03.889
♪ I want to drown my sorrow ♪

691
00:34:03.971 --> 00:34:10.538
♪ No tomorrow. no tomorrow ♪

692
00:34:10.620 --> 00:34:13.196
♪ I find it kind of funny ♪

693
00:34:13.279 --> 00:34:15.895
♪ I find it kind of sad ♪

694
00:34:15.978 --> 00:34:18.514
♪ The dreams in
which I'm dying ♪

695
00:34:18.597 --> 00:34:20.175
-♪ Are the best I've ever had ♪
-She's crashing.

696
00:34:21.421 --> 00:34:23.041
Pulse is 31. No heartbeat.

697
00:34:23.124 --> 00:34:24.495
Put the
output curve to maximum.

698
00:34:24.578 --> 00:34:25.576
100 beats per minute.

699
00:34:25.659 --> 00:34:27.030
Cap. what can I do?

700
00:34:27.113 --> 00:34:29.357
♪ When people run in circles ♪

701
00:34:29.440 --> 00:34:32.805
♪ It's a very. very ♪

702
00:34:32.887 --> 00:34:36.502
♪ Mad world ♪

703
00:34:38.413 --> 00:34:41.862
♪ Mad world ♪

704
00:34:43.565 --> 00:34:44.313
♪ Children waiting ♪

705
00:34:44.396 --> 00:34:46.141
♪ For the day they... ♪

706
00:34:46.224 --> 00:34:47.678
Coming up on capture.

707
00:34:47.761 --> 00:34:54.200
♪ Happy birthday.
happy birthday ♪

708
00:34:54.283 --> 00:34:57.566
♪ And I feel the way that
every child should... ♪

709
00:34:57.648 --> 00:34:58.923
Transcutaneous pacing.

710
00:34:59.725 --> 00:35:00.889
Ready?

711
00:35:00.971 --> 00:35:01.928
Hold on.

712
00:35:02.010 --> 00:35:05.085
♪ Sit and listen ♪

713
00:35:05.168 --> 00:35:09.073
♪ Went to school and I
was very nervous... ♪

714
00:35:09.156 --> 00:35:10.070
Initiating

715
00:35:10.153 --> 00:35:11.816
in three. two. one.

716
00:35:12.978 --> 00:35:15.886
♪ No one knew me ♪

717
00:35:15.969 --> 00:35:18.462
♪ Hello. teacher. tell me ♪

718
00:35:18.545 --> 00:35:20.248
♪ What's my lesson? ♪

719
00:35:20.331 --> 00:35:22.783
Chest
muscles contracting.

720
00:35:22.866 --> 00:35:23.946
Keep that going.

721
00:35:24.028 --> 00:35:25.899
I got a sinus rhythm.

722
00:35:25.982 --> 00:35:27.560
-She's stabilizing.
-Okay. okay.

723
00:35:27.643 --> 00:35:29.347
Good. good. Well done. guys.

724
00:35:29.430 --> 00:35:33.210
♪ Funny. I find it kind of sad ♪

725
00:35:33.293 --> 00:35:36.534
♪ The dreams in which I'm
dying are the best... ♪

726
00:35:36.617 --> 00:35:38.404
I've got affected
areas on her hands.

727
00:35:38.486 --> 00:35:41.768
arms. upper torso. neck. and
face. but no apparent injury.

728
00:35:41.851 --> 00:35:43.804
On this hand. it's like
a knife wound. right?

729
00:35:44.220 --> 00:35:45.881
Or a soup can wound.

730
00:35:45.964 --> 00:35:48.748
Foodborne bacteria and she
didn't get it checked out.

731
00:35:50.160 --> 00:35:52.529
Or didn't care to.

732
00:35:52.611 --> 00:35:54.066
Let's get in the ambulance.
try to keep her alive

733
00:35:54.148 --> 00:35:55.520
en route to the
hospital. Come on.

734
00:35:55.603 --> 00:35:58.635
♪ Mad world ♪

735
00:36:00.920 --> 00:36:04.036
♪ Mad world. ♪

736
00:36:12.054 --> 00:36:14.049
You're restocking the ambulance?

737
00:36:14.131 --> 00:36:15.544
I had some free time.

738
00:36:15.627 --> 00:36:17.123
Thought I'd put it to good use.

739
00:36:18.078 --> 00:36:19.366
Well. it looks good.

740
00:36:20.612 --> 00:36:22.690
It smells good.

741
00:36:22.772 --> 00:36:24.850
Mm. That's the air freshener.

742
00:36:24.933 --> 00:36:26.429
-Oh.
-You know me...

743
00:36:26.512 --> 00:36:27.467
always ready.

744
00:36:27.549 --> 00:36:28.797
No matter the environment.

745
00:36:28.879 --> 00:36:30.624
-Uh-huh.
-Does anyone want

746
00:36:30.707 --> 00:36:31.830
an afternoon pick-me-up?

747
00:36:31.912 --> 00:36:33.616
Vanilla latte.

748
00:36:33.698 --> 00:36:35.610
With oat milk. Extra hot.

749
00:36:35.692 --> 00:36:36.856
Thanks. Buck.

750
00:36:38.102 --> 00:36:39.433
You're bringing her coffee?

751
00:36:39.515 --> 00:36:41.385
Uh. you're restocking
already stocked ambulances.

752
00:36:41.468 --> 00:36:43.836
Okay. guys. this is
getting a little...

753
00:36:43.919 --> 00:36:44.999
Firefighter Wilson.

754
00:36:45.081 --> 00:36:47.075
Just the person I
was looking for.

755
00:36:49.402 --> 00:36:51.023
Oh.

756
00:36:51.105 --> 00:36:53.516
I'm the 118 Firefighter
of the Month?

757
00:36:53.599 --> 00:36:55.635
-Since when is this a thing?
-That certificate

758
00:36:55.717 --> 00:36:57.047
is suitable for framing.

759
00:36:57.130 --> 00:36:59.248
Plus. it comes with
a $50 gift card.

760
00:36:59.331 --> 00:37:02.157
-Oh. so it's a bribe.
-How much was that latte. Buck?

761
00:37:02.239 --> 00:37:03.403
I used petty cash.

762
00:37:03.486 --> 00:37:04.608
Oh. so you bribed her

763
00:37:04.691 --> 00:37:06.270
with other people's money. Okay.

764
00:37:06.352 --> 00:37:07.806
You're making up fake
awards so she can take you

765
00:37:07.889 --> 00:37:09.136
-as her plus-one.
-I don't need

766
00:37:09.219 --> 00:37:10.881
to make up fake awards.

767
00:37:10.964 --> 00:37:12.751
And it sounds as if you
don't think she deserves it.

768
00:37:12.834 --> 00:37:14.579
Well. I disagree.

769
00:37:14.661 --> 00:37:15.742
Congratulations. Firefighter.

770
00:37:15.825 --> 00:37:17.694
And. by the way. if
you were to choose me.

771
00:37:17.777 --> 00:37:19.564
just know that I wouldn't
be going as your boss...

772
00:37:19.647 --> 00:37:20.893
I'd be going as
your best friend.

773
00:37:20.975 --> 00:37:22.929
Oh. come on. We're
gonna play that card?

774
00:37:23.011 --> 00:37:25.007
Nearly two decades
as her best friend.

775
00:37:25.089 --> 00:37:27.292
That's not a card.
That's a full deck.

776
00:37:27.374 --> 00:37:29.493
-We are still best friends. right. Hen?
-Chim.

777
00:37:29.576 --> 00:37:31.445
Maybe I should
play the "guy who actually"

778
00:37:31.528 --> 00:37:33.274
"saved Hauser's life" card.

779
00:37:33.357 --> 00:37:35.268
No one told you
to jump off of that bridge.

780
00:37:35.351 --> 00:37:36.390
You get no card.

781
00:37:36.472 --> 00:37:37.885
I didn't need to be told.

782
00:37:37.967 --> 00:37:40.336
Actually. Diaz. you
do need to be told

783
00:37:40.419 --> 00:37:42.704
to do something like that.
You don't just jump in.

784
00:37:42.786 --> 00:37:44.366
That's stupid and
reckless. like Buck.

785
00:37:44.449 --> 00:37:46.651
In fact. you should probably
be written up for something

786
00:37:46.734 --> 00:37:48.977
-like that.
-I'll remember that. Han.

787
00:37:49.060 --> 00:37:50.223
That's "Captain Han" to you.

788
00:37:50.306 --> 00:37:51.802
You're just a temp.

789
00:37:51.884 --> 00:37:54.087
You know what? I didn't
even want to go to space.

790
00:37:54.169 --> 00:37:55.250
But you know what
feels good right now?

791
00:37:55.333 --> 00:37:56.414
Space.

792
00:37:56.496 --> 00:37:58.117
Give me some.

793
00:38:10.621 --> 00:38:12.200
We're treating the
infection with antibiotics.

794
00:38:12.283 --> 00:38:13.945
Has she woken up?

795
00:38:14.028 --> 00:38:15.316
-Said anything?
-She's been unconscious

796
00:38:15.399 --> 00:38:17.352
since she was brought in.

797
00:38:17.435 --> 00:38:19.470
Though. given her wounds.

798
00:38:19.553 --> 00:38:21.215
that might not be
the worst thing.

799
00:38:23.417 --> 00:38:24.955
Right.

800
00:38:25.038 --> 00:38:26.408
Did our staff speak

801
00:38:26.491 --> 00:38:29.399
with you about tracking
down Ms. Moningham's family?

802
00:38:29.482 --> 00:38:31.477
She didn't have an
emergency contact on record.

803
00:38:31.560 --> 00:38:34.468
No. we haven't found anyone yet.

804
00:38:34.551 --> 00:38:35.839
I hope you do.

805
00:38:37.376 --> 00:38:39.494
It makes a difference
if someone cares.

806
00:38:48.135 --> 00:38:49.507
I come in peace.

807
00:38:49.590 --> 00:38:51.626
Also with lager.

808
00:38:51.708 --> 00:38:54.077
You gonna write
me up if I say no?

809
00:38:54.160 --> 00:38:57.774
No. I've laid down the weapons
of intergalactic war. okay?

810
00:38:59.020 --> 00:39:00.059
All right.

811
00:39:05.294 --> 00:39:07.869
Technically. I think we
should be at Hen's doorstep

812
00:39:07.952 --> 00:39:08.992
with these apology beers.

813
00:39:09.075 --> 00:39:10.154
Yeah.

814
00:39:10.237 --> 00:39:12.148
I already tried calling her.

815
00:39:12.231 --> 00:39:13.645
She sent me to voicemail.

816
00:39:13.727 --> 00:39:14.808
Me. too.

817
00:39:20.291 --> 00:39:23.199
You know everybody's really glad
that you're in charge. right?

818
00:39:24.446 --> 00:39:27.188
I spend half the day
trying to convince myself

819
00:39:27.271 --> 00:39:29.099
that I can actually do
this and the other half

820
00:39:29.181 --> 00:39:30.802
waiting for Chief Simpson
to finally tell me

821
00:39:30.884 --> 00:39:32.399
he's found a real
captain to take over.

822
00:39:33.585 --> 00:39:35.538
You could be the real captain.

823
00:39:35.621 --> 00:39:37.325
All you got to do is
take that damned test.

824
00:39:37.408 --> 00:39:39.111
I don't know why you won't.

825
00:39:40.606 --> 00:39:42.185
It just doesn't seem
right. you know?

826
00:39:42.268 --> 00:39:44.429
It feels... disrespectful

827
00:39:44.512 --> 00:39:47.253
for me. of all people. to try
to step into Bobby's shoes.

828
00:39:48.209 --> 00:39:49.996
Mm.

829
00:39:50.079 --> 00:39:51.367
Yeah. these last six months

830
00:39:51.449 --> 00:39:53.278
without Bobby have
been tough enough.

831
00:39:53.361 --> 00:39:55.397
Someone coming in
from the outside?

832
00:39:55.479 --> 00:39:57.183
They won't stand a chance.

833
00:39:58.138 --> 00:39:59.550
We're lucky to have you.

834
00:40:00.922 --> 00:40:02.085
Most of the time.

835
00:40:02.168 --> 00:40:04.120
Thanks.

836
00:40:07.194 --> 00:40:08.317
I miss him.

837
00:40:10.476 --> 00:40:12.139
Me. too.

838
00:40:12.221 --> 00:40:15.213
Truth is. I don't want to go
to space.

839
00:40:15.296 --> 00:40:17.373
I-I don't even like
flying domestically.

840
00:40:18.578 --> 00:40:20.323
But Chim was yelling at Eddie

841
00:40:20.406 --> 00:40:22.150
and Eddie was yelling
at Chim and...

842
00:40:23.355 --> 00:40:26.056
I just... I didn't want
to be left out. you know?

843
00:40:28.174 --> 00:40:31.664
The-the weird part was...

844
00:40:31.747 --> 00:40:34.115
after Hen walked away...

845
00:40:35.445 --> 00:40:37.148
...I-I turned around...

846
00:40:38.394 --> 00:40:40.596
...half expecting
to see Bobby there.

847
00:40:42.175 --> 00:40:45.125
Shaking his head and
giving me that...

848
00:40:45.208 --> 00:40:47.120
"what were you thinking?"
face.

849
00:40:50.110 --> 00:40:52.105
Uh. o-obviously. he...

850
00:40:52.187 --> 00:40:53.849
he wasn't there.

851
00:40:56.882 --> 00:40:59.332
I even miss his looks
of disappointment.

852
00:41:01.992 --> 00:41:03.280
Buck.

853
00:41:03.362 --> 00:41:04.941
You have to stop.
It's past his bedtime.

854
00:41:05.024 --> 00:41:06.977
Yeah. yeah.

855
00:41:08.722 --> 00:41:10.425
Say good night. Buck.

856
00:41:12.253 --> 00:41:13.874
Okay.

857
00:41:13.956 --> 00:41:15.550
We'll pick this up tomorrow.

858
00:41:18.526 --> 00:41:21.933
I went to see
Gina in the hospital today.

859
00:41:22.016 --> 00:41:24.135
I don't think she
was always this way.

860
00:41:24.218 --> 00:41:25.672
She...

861
00:41:25.755 --> 00:41:28.622
had a different life before.

862
00:41:28.704 --> 00:41:31.572
People who cared. People
who would've called.

863
00:41:31.655 --> 00:41:34.562
Can't help but wonder if...

864
00:41:34.645 --> 00:41:38.426
they stopped calling or
she stopped answering or...

865
00:41:39.423 --> 00:41:41.708
She's not you.

866
00:41:47.815 --> 00:41:49.934
It's hard.

867
00:41:50.017 --> 00:41:52.509
being around people
who loved him.

868
00:41:52.592 --> 00:41:53.797
Even my own kids.

869
00:41:53.880 --> 00:41:55.709
I know that sounds crazy. but...

870
00:41:57.328 --> 00:41:58.450
...that's how I feel.

871
00:41:59.655 --> 00:42:02.106
That's why I didn't
go to the dedication.

872
00:42:02.189 --> 00:42:03.976
I mean. I knew it was important.

873
00:42:04.059 --> 00:42:06.012
And Lord knows he
deserved the honor.

874
00:42:06.095 --> 00:42:08.753
But I also knew that I
couldn't take sitting there.

875
00:42:08.836 --> 00:42:12.077
listening to all the
great Bobby Nash stories.

876
00:42:12.160 --> 00:42:13.489
It just hurt too much.

877
00:42:14.735 --> 00:42:16.522
I don't want to talk about him.

878
00:42:17.519 --> 00:42:19.638
I just want to talk to him.

879
00:42:20.842 --> 00:42:23.003
And I can't do that.

880
00:42:23.085 --> 00:42:24.664
Ever again.

881
00:42:27.615 --> 00:42:29.110
Athena.

882
00:42:30.315 --> 00:42:34.719
You get to take whatever time
and grieve however you need.

883
00:42:36.006 --> 00:42:39.371
Karen and I are gonna keep
inviting you to dinner.

884
00:42:39.454 --> 00:42:41.407
-no matter how many times you turn us down.
-Mm.

885
00:42:42.820 --> 00:42:47.099
We ain't gonna never
stop calling you.

886
00:42:47.181 --> 00:42:48.595
Oh. don't you worry about me.

887
00:42:48.677 --> 00:42:51.087
I have learned my lesson.

888
00:42:53.330 --> 00:42:55.075
Next invitation I get.

889
00:42:55.158 --> 00:42:58.233
the answer is yes.
